this resolution, agreed to on the 15th of May,
stated the intention to be totally to suppress the
exercise of every kind of authority under the
British crown. .

On the 7th of June certain resolutions respect-
ing independence were moved and seconded. On
the 10th of June it was resolved that a committee
should be appointed to prepare a declaration to the
following effect: “That the United Colonies are,
and of right ought to be, free and independent
states; that they are absolved from all allegiance
to the British crown, -and that all political connec-
tion between them and the State of ‘Great "Britain

, is, and ought to be, totally dissolved.”

