NEW YORK’S PROCREATION COMMISSION.
The Procreation Commission of New York State,

created by an act of the Legislature, is to examine

into the mental and physical condition and the

record and family history of the feeble-minded,”

epileptic criminal and other defective inmates con-
ﬁned in the State hospitals, reformatories, charitable
and penal intitutions; and if in the judgment of
the majority of the board procreation by any such
person would produce children with an inherited
tendency to crime, insanity, feeble—mindedness,
idiocy, or imbecility, and there is no probability of
an improvement in their condition,’ then the board
shall appoint one of their number to perform such
operation for the prevention of procreation that
shall be decided to be most effective. All orders
made, under this law are subject to review by the
Supreme Court. The board consists of three mem-
bers (all physicians) appointed by the Governor.

