law, why a set of words upon parchment should
convey the dominion of land; Why the son ‘should
have a right to exclude his fellow creatures from

a determinate spot of ground because his father,

had done so before him, or why the occupier of a
particular ﬁeld or of a jewel, when lying on his

death bed and no longer able to maintain possession,

should be entitled to tell the rest of the world
which of fchem should enjoy it after him.——-Sir
William Blackstone in his commentaries. Book ll,
