Public Health Service, and is issued by the Federal
Treasury Department, of which the Health Service
is a subordinate bureau. The authors are B. S.
Warren and Edgar Sydenstricker, respectively sur-
geon and statistician of the bureau. The pamphlet,
which contains 79 pages, is at once a statement of
health conditions, particularly among the wage-
earners, and an argument for government health
insurance.

