“thateach of the 30,000,000 workers in the.United
States losses; on the average about nine days every
year on‘ account of sickness alone.” This estimate,
it is pointed out, very nearly coincides with the
German and English figures, for more than 26,000,000
industrial workers, which show an average of eight
to nine days of illness per year through a number
of years. Putting the average daily wage at $2,
says the bulletin, and the cost of medical attention
at $1 per day, the annual loss would be $800,000,000.
