The evidence before the committee shows that it
is the custom of the company where steel and iron
plants are established and towns and vil ages grow
up around the company’s plants, through a subsi-
diary company known as the Union Supply Co.,
to open stores to supply its employees with gro-
ceries, provisions, and almost every article of

household necessity, together with powder, fuse and

other supplies——1n fact everything the employees
need, either to live or conduct their operations as
employees of the company,

The local grocer, baker, meat and fish dealer,
apothecary, blacksmith, carpenter, coal, wood, and
other dealers are thus brought into direct compe-

