WHAT LABOR GETS FROM THE RAILROADS.

One frequently hears or reads the statement that
more than 70 per cent. of the railroad revenues are
expended for labor and material. The statement is
misleading. There is no reason for lumping ma-
terial with labor, since virtually all material pur-
chased by the railroads has already paid from two
to ﬁve capitalist proﬁts in the various transactions
through which it has passed. The share of labor in
railroad revenues cannot be absolutely determined,
but thanks to the ﬁgures of the Interstate Com-
merce Commission, it can be approximated.

