rumblings in ‘Wall Street at the time he consented
to this remarkable merger cannot be doubted. In
the light of subsequent events, it is equally cer-
tain that it was the receding and not an approach-
ing storm which disturbed him. In an editorial on
June 7, 1911, published in the New York World, it
was clearly demonstrated that the panic was over
prior to the interview between Colonel Roosevelt
and the representatives of the Steel Corporation.

