poration owed its succes‘s and its permanency. to
the power and the skill of the ﬁnanciers who had
created and the iron masters who had directed its
operations. Since that time its dominance has been
due in no small measure to the sudden, i1l-consid-
ered, and arbitrary ﬁat of the Chief Executive.

 

