are the privilege of the writ of habeas corpus, the
right to jury trial, to free speech, to peaceful
assemblage, to keep and bear arms, to be free from
unreasonable searches and seizures, to speedy pub-
lic trial and to freedom from excessive bail and
from cruel and unusual punishments.

